<li id="cite_note-Williams-7"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Williams_7-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Williams_7-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFDon_B._Williams2004" class="citation book cs1">Don B. Williams (December 2004). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=tbnQ6doL2U8C"><i>Slavery in Utah Territory: 1847–1865</i></a>. Mt Zion Books. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780974607627" title="Special:BookSources/9780974607627"><bdi>9780974607627</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Slavery+in+Utah+Territory%3A+1847%E2%80%931865&amp;rft.pub=Mt+Zion+Books&amp;rft.date=2004-12&amp;rft.isbn=9780974607627&amp;rft.au=Don+B.+Williams&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DtbnQ6doL2U8C&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACivil+rights+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-8"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFCollier1987" class="citation book cs1">Collier, Fred C. (1987). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=LkRZGQ8oO8IC&amp;pg=PA26"><i>The Teachings of President Brigham Young Vol. 3 1852–1854</i></a>. Colliers Publishing Co. pp.&#160;26–29. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0934964017" title="Special:BookSources/0934964017"><bdi>0934964017</bdi></a><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">19 August</span> 2017</span>. <q>[I]nasmuch as we believe in the Bible, … we must believe in Slavery. This colored race have [sic] been subjected to severe curses, which they have … brought upon themselves. … I am a firm believer in Slavery. … A strong abolitionist feeling has power over [many brethren] and they commence to whisper … 'I am afraid it is not right.' I know [slavery] is right, and there should be a law made to have the slaves serve their masters, because they are not capable of ruling themselves. … I am firm in the belief that they ought to dwell in servitude. … When a master has a Negro, and uses him well, [the slave] is much better off than if he was free. … good wholesome servitude, I know there is nothing better than that.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Teachings+of+President+Brigham+Young+Vol.+3+1852%E2%80%931854&amp;rft.pages=26-29&amp;rft.pub=Colliers+Publishing+Co.&amp;rft.date=1987&amp;rft.isbn=0934964017&amp;rft.aulast=Collier&amp;rft.aufirst=Fred+C.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DLkRZGQ8oO8IC%26pg%3DPA26&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACivil+rights+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-9"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFWatt1852" class="citation journal cs1">Watt, George D. (23 January 1852). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://catalog.churchofjesuschrist.org/record/1622c13d-95e8-440c-a32f-4db4d4134430?view=browse">"Speech by Governor Young in Joint Session of the Legislature, giving counsel on a bill in relation to African Slavery, given at Salt Lake City, on Friday, January 23rd, 1852"</a>. <i>Brigham Young Papers</i>. History Department of the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints: 1–3<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">15 October</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Brigham+Young+Papers&amp;rft.atitle=Speech+by+Governor+Young+in+Joint+Session+of+the+Legislature%2C+giving+counsel+on+a+bill+in+relation+to+African+Slavery%2C+given+at+Salt+Lake+City%2C+on+Friday%2C+January+23rd%2C+1852&amp;rft.pages=1-3&amp;rft.date=1852-01-23&amp;rft.aulast=Watt&amp;rft.aufirst=George+D.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fcatalog.churchofjesuschrist.org%2Frecord%2F1622c13d-95e8-440c-a32f-4db4d4134430%3Fview%3Dbrowse&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACivil+rights+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-10"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Brigham Young told Greeley: "If slaves are brought here by those who owned them in the states, we do not favor their escape from the service of their owners." (see Greeley, <i>Overland Journey</i> 211–212) quoted in <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFTerry_L._Givens,_Philip_L._Barlow2015" class="citation book cs1">Terry L. Givens, Philip L. Barlow (September 2015). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=Es4fCgAAQBAJ"><i>The Oxford Handbook of Mormonism</i></a>. Oxford University Press. p.&#160;383. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-19-977841-6" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-19-977841-6"><bdi>978-0-19-977841-6</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Oxford+Handbook+of+Mormonism&amp;rft.pages=383&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2015-09&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-19-977841-6&amp;rft.au=Terry+L.+Givens%2C+Philip+L.+Barlow&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DEs4fCgAAQBAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACivil+rights+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
