<li id="cite_note-68"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-68">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFIber2001" class="citation book cs1">Iber, Jorge (2001). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=U5yVltlFKP0C&amp;pg=PA55"><i>Hispanics in the Mormon Zion, 1912-1999</i></a> (2001 Paperback&#160;ed.). College Station, TX: Texas A&amp;M University Press. p.&#160;55. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1585442054" title="Special:BookSources/1585442054"><bdi>1585442054</bdi></a>. <q>Prior to 1930 Utah's predominantly Mormon population (65 percent classified as practicing Mormons in 1930) took justifiable pride in its tradition of self-sufficiency.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Hispanics+in+the+Mormon+Zion%2C+1912-1999&amp;rft.place=College+Station%2C+TX&amp;rft.pages=55&amp;rft.edition=2001+Paperback&amp;rft.pub=Texas+A%26M+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2001&amp;rft.isbn=1585442054&amp;rft.aulast=Iber&amp;rft.aufirst=Jorge&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DU5yVltlFKP0C%26pg%3DPA55&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACivil+rights+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
